**Expected Behavior**: Fails with `error CS8400: Feature 'instance member in 'nameof'' is not available in C# 8.0. Please use language version 12.0 or greater.`

**Actual Behavior**: Fails with `error CS7038: Failed to emit module 'TestProject': Unable to determine specific cause of the failure.`

**Note**: Originally reported by a customer internally over e-mail.

This is also a regression (no error is reported by for example Roslyn [5.0.0-2.26075.103](https://dev.azure.com/dnceng/public/_artifacts/feed/dotnet-tools/NuGet/Microsoft.Net.Compilers.Toolset/overview/5.0.0-2.26075.103) (https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn/commit/123b078829e8fdb3055704d609b7b5a44e1537dd)), so we need to decide whether the langversion error should be reported or this should successfully compile again.

## Description

This PR removes the Crossgen2Composite condition that previously caused ExcludeList to be ignored when building composite R2R images. In addition, it removes entry-point assembly initialization that was producing incorrect msbuild metadata.


<img width="1182" height="165" alt="Screenshot 2026-02-19 at 13 55 22" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fe330a26-8754-482d-890f-624a072d4626" />


That metadata is not used in composite mode and was corrupting the msbuild metadata of the entry-point assembly, which invalidated the R2R target’s caching mechanism.
```
if (!_createCompositeImage)
{
    _inputAssembly = CompilationEntry.ItemSpec;  // Only used in non-composite
}
else
{
    _inputAssembly = "CompositeImage";  // Composite mode ignores ItemSpec
}
```
